Interface IMessage

All Superinterfaces:
IDataPacketData, java.io.Serializable
All Known Subinterfaces:
IAddCmdMessage, IErrorMessage, IExceptionMessage, IFailureMessage, IImageMessage, IJoinMessage, ILeaveMessage, IPoemMessage, IRejectMessage, IRequestCmdMessage, IStringMessage
All Known Implementing Classes:
AddCmdMessage, ErrorMessage, ExceptionMessage, FailureMessage, ImageData, JoinData, LeaveData, PoemData, RejectMessage, RequestCmdMessage, StringData
public interface IMessage
extends IDataPacketData
Interface for messages used for type narrowing purposes. This is used to define well known types in this system. Similar to how you created your own tasks in HW07, if you would like to create more well known types for your system, every type you make would need to implement this interface to be received by IChatAppReceivers.
